
Enhance Quecumber with a full Advanced Analytics system for Owners.
Stack:
* Next.js 14 (App Router)
* Supabase (PostgreSQL)
* Recharts (charts)
* TailwindCSS
* next-intl
Goal: Transform the analytics dashboard into a powerful decision-making interface with staff performance tracking, queue health scoring, and predictive trends.

1️⃣ MAIN ANALYTICS DASHBOARD
Route: /admin/analytics/[locationId]
Add date range selector:
* Today
* Last 7 days
* Last 30 days
* Custom range
All metrics must respect selected date range.

2️⃣ CORE KPI CARDS (Top Section)
Show animated KPI cards:
* Total Customers Served
* Average Wait Time
* Average Service Time
* No-Show Rate (%)
* Peak Hour
Each card must:
* Show % change vs previous period
* Color-coded trend indicator (green ↑ red ↓)
Use aggregated SQL queries.

3️⃣ STAFF PERFORMANCE LEADERBOARD
Section: “Staff Performance”
Show:
* Staff Name
* Total Served
* Avg Service Time
* Efficiency Score
Efficiency Score Formula: (Total Served / Avg Service Time) normalized per location
Add:
* Sort by performance
* Highlight top performer
Only OWNER and SENIOR can view.

4️⃣ QUEUE HEALTH SCORE SYSTEM
Create a computed metric:
Queue Health Score (0–100)
Formula factors:
* Avg Wait Time vs target
* No-show rate
* Current load vs avg load
Output: 🟢 Smooth (80–100) 🟡 Busy (50–79) 🔴 Overloaded (<50)
Display:
* Circular progress indicator
* Explanation tooltip

5️⃣ HOURLY HEATMAP
Build: Day vs Hour heatmap grid
Rows: Monday → Sunday
Columns: 9AM → 9PM (or business hours)
Color intensity based on: Number of queue entries created
Use aggregated SQL grouped by: EXTRACT(DOW) EXTRACT(HOUR)

6️⃣ SERVICE TYPE ANALYSIS
Section: “Service Insights”
Show:
* Most popular queue_type
* Distribution pie chart
* Avg wait per queue_type
* Avg service time per queue_type
Use grouped SQL queries.

7️⃣ TREND CHART (Last 30 Days)
Line chart:
* Daily served count
* Overlay avg wait time
Purpose: Show growth or decline.

8️⃣ PREDICTIVE BASIC TREND (V1 LIGHT)
Add simple moving average:
* 7-day rolling average
Display subtle forecast arrow: “Demand trending up” “Demand stable” “Demand declining”
No ML — simple statistical smoothing.

9️⃣ SQL OPTIMIZATION
Create SQL views:
* location_daily_metrics
* staff_performance_metrics
* service_type_metrics
* hourly_distribution
Add indexes on:
* location_id
* created_at
* served_at
Avoid N+1 queries.

🔟 UI DESIGN REQUIREMENTS
* Bold modern SaaS
* Clean spacing
* Soft shadows
* Smooth chart animations
* Dark/light mode compatible
Layout:
* KPI row
* Health score + Leaderboard
* Heatmap full width
* Service + Trend charts
Mobile responsive.

SECURITY
Enforce:
* Only OWNER can see financial-scale metrics
* SENIOR can see limited performance view
* JUNIOR cannot access analytics
Respect RLS.

Deliver:
* Complete route
* SQL view definitions
* Recharts components
* Optimized data fetching
* Modular analytics components
Keep architecture scalable for future revenue analytics.